definition.value: Gewürztraminerwine is a white wine varietal produced entirely from Gewürztraminer grapes.
Gewürztraminer is an aromatic wine grape variety, used in white wines, and performs best in cooler climates.
Carignane wine is a red wine varietal produced entirely from Carignane grapes.
Carignan (also known as Carignane) is a red grape variety of Spanish origin that is more commonly found in French wine but is widely planted throughout the western Mediterranean and around the globe.
Grenache wine is a red wine varietal produced entirely from Grenache grapes.
Grenache is one of the most widely planted red wine grape varieties in the world.
Barbera wine is a red wine varietal produced entirely from Barbera grapes.

Barbera is a red Italian wine grape variety that, as of 2000, was the third most-planted red grape variety in Italy (after Sangiovese and Montepulciano). It produces good yields and is known for deep color, full body, low tannins and high levels of acid.

Tagliatelle is a traditional type of egg pasta from the Emilia-Romagna and Marche regions of Italy. Individual pieces of tagliatelle are long, flat ribbons that are similar in shape to fettuccine and are typically about 6.5 to 10 mm (0.26 to 0.39 in) wide.

Tortellini are ring-shaped pasta, sometimes also described as "navel shaped", hence their alternative name of "belly button" (ombelico). They are typically stuffed with a mix of meat (pork loin, raw prosciutto, Mortadella), and Parmigiano Reggiano cheese.
Tortelloni are stuffed pasta, the same shape as tortellini, but larger. They are usually stuffed with ricotta cheese and leaf vegetables, such as spinach.
Tortiglioni are a type of pasta, similar to rigatoni but larger and with deeper grooves which spiral around the pasta.

Fusilli are a variety of pasta that are formed into corkscrew or helical shapes. The word fusilli presumably comes from fuso ("spindle"), as traditionally it is "spun" by pressing and rolling a small rod over the thin strips of pasta to wind them around it in a corkscrew shape.
Conchiglie, commonly known as "shells" or "seashells" is a type of pasta. It is usually sold in the plain durum wheat variety. The shell shape of the pasta allows the sauce to adhere to it.

Linguine is a type of pasta similar to fettuccine and trenette but elliptical in section rather than flat. It is about 4 millimetres in width, which is wider than spaghetti but not as wide as fettuccine.

Penne is an extruded type of pasta with cylinder-shaped pieces, their ends cut at a bias. It is lexically related to Latin penna (meaning "feather" or "quill"), and was originally intended to imitate the then-ubiquitous fountain pen's steel nibs.

Zakynthos Wine is wine produced on the Greek island of Zakynthos (Zante) in the Ionian Sea. A wide array of native Ionian grape varieties have been planted on the island for centuries, and are most famously used to make the intensely flavored, highly acidic Verdea wine.
The Cabernet Sauvignon grape plant originates from a cross between Cabernet Franc and Sauvignon blanc varieties. It produces Cabernet Sauvignon grapes, a red wine grape variety.
Any wine produced in the Bordeaux region of southwest France.
A preserved food, where the moisture levels in the food product have been reduced to low levels to improve shelf life.
A food product organized by the process which it results from.
A food which has its flavour or taste enhanced by some process which may include the addition of flavourings.
Food that has undergone a broiling or grilling process.
A method of precooking food where a liquid is heated to just below the boiling point. Often used to retard the spoiling of milk.
Milled food is food ground into smaller particles as a result of a milling process.
A food product traditionally consumed during supper.
A food product traditionally consumed during lunch.
Food products manufactured from various nutritional components made to resemble conventional protein-source foods in texture such as meat, seafood, or poultry.
Toasted food is is the output of a toasting process.
A food product that is derived from some pig.
A lipid food product is a food product made primarily of plant or animal fat or oil
Quick bread is any bread leavened with leavening agents other than yeast or eggs.
Almond bark (also known as vanilla flavored candy coating) is a chocolate-like confection made with vegetable fats instead of cocoa butter and with coloring and flavors added

Allspice is the dried unripe fruit (berries, used as a spice) of Pimenta dioica, a midcanopy tree native to the Greater Antilles, southern Mexico, and Central America, now cultivated in many warm parts of the world.
An anchovy fillet is a fish fillet taken from an anchovy fish.
A sprout from an alfalfa seed.
A chicken nugget is a chicken product made from chicken meat that is breaded or battered, then deep-fried or baked.
